ChangeLog

0.9.3
  * Ported Qt GUI from Qt4/KDE4 to Qt5 with CMake integration.
  * Qt GUI: Font selection menu, tab support, MCD panel, tooltips.
  * Unified version info between ncurses and Qt builds.
  * All config files (including qtkeyset.cfg) use versioned templates.
  * Settings saved on exit in Qt build.
  * Auto-generate all 5 default config files when missing.
  * Debian packaging: Qt5 build dependency and desktop entry added.

0.9.1
  * Modernized for Ubuntu 22.04+ and GCC 12+ environments.
  * Build system: CMake 3.10+ required.
  * Comprehensive code quality improvements (60+ bug fixes):
    - Fixed memory safety: NULL dereferences, buffer overflows,
      uninitialized variables, use-after-free, memory leaks.
    - Fixed threading: pthread_cond_timedwait absolute time,
      mutex lock/unlock pairing, va_copy for va_list reuse.
    - Fixed logic errors: operator< self-comparison, && vs ||
      range checks, dup2 argument order, switch fall-through.
    - Fixed security: replaced system() shell injection with
      fork+exec and safe C APIs, inet_ntoa replaced with inet_ntop.
    - Fixed type safety: ullong changed to unsigned long long,
      ssize_t used for error detection from libssh2_sftp_read.
    - Fixed build: sizeof(pointer) bug after VLA-to-vector conversion,
      libssh2_session_startup replaced with libssh2_session_handshake.
    - Fixed dead code: semicolons truncating tar extract -C directory,
      format string argument count mismatches.

0.9.0
  * Build packaging changed from automake to cmake.
  * Fix compile warnings.
  * Fixed syntax highlighter in internal editor.

0.8.1
  * Support console transparency.
  * Bug-fix - compress cancel.
  * fix linm.sh, linm.csh.
  * quick search reinforcement
  * shell mode cursor bugfix.

0.8
  * configure menu add.
  * libssh2-0.18 update.
  * rar, iso add.
  * editor text replace menu add.

0.7.12
  * samba connect supported.
  * file copy progressbar bugfix.
  * remote copy overwrite message bugfix.
  * FreeBSD, GCC 2.9x compile error fix.
